Example:

  # View
  <%= text_field_with_local_auto_complete :post, title, entries %>

By default, local_auto_complete_for limits the results to 10 entries,
and sorts by the given field.

local_auto_complete_for takes a forth parameter, an options hash to
the find method used to search for the records:

  auto_complete_for :post, :title, entries, :limit => 15, :order => 'created_at DESC'

For more examples, see script.aculo.us:
* http://wiki.github.com/madrobby/scriptaculous/autocompleter-local
